{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"958d2ecb-24dc-412d-8774-bed7183a6578","content":"No files found in the workspace — I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your ContentPage root element:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <StackLayout Padding=\"20\">\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Slider Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is adding:\n- `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"` — imports your namespace\n- `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — enables compiled bindings\n\nYour existing `{Binding ...}` expressions stay the same. The compiler now resolves them against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n**2. Catch binding errors at build time** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, any `{Binding}` referencing a property that doesn't exist on `SettingsViewModel` (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`) will produce a **compile-time error** instead of silently failing at runtime.\n\n**3. Opting out locally** — if a subtree binds to a different type (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate`), set a new `x:DataType` there, or use `x:DataType=\"\"` to disable compiled bindings for that scope:\n\n```xml\n<CollectionView ItemsSource=\"{Binding Items}\">\n    <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>\n        <DataTemplate x:DataType=\"vm:ItemViewModel\">\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding Name}\" />\n        </DataTemplate>\n    </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>\n</CollectionView>\n```\n\n**Summary:** `x:DataType` is the only XAML change needed — no binding syntax changes required. Misspelled or missing properties become build errors.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"59783e18-c7c8-449b-b0e3-f02c0edc7300","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The files don't exist yet. The user described what they have — a SettingsPage.xaml with plain bindings and a SettingsViewModel. They want me to show them how to convert to compiled bindings. Since there are no actual files, I'll provide the guidance directly.","outputTokens":699},"id":"6266539a-243f-4486-ada7-7119022c5542","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:00:05.632Z","parentId":"5b2b6ea7-c171-4eda-b5fe-ecb624d4ef82"}
